can dogs suffer from depression or is it my imagination i recently took my lab on a family vacation we stayed in a cabin on a lake he learned to swim and fetch things he was free to roam without a chain or a leash i would take him on long walks on old logging trails when we returned to the city he seems lethargic and depressed it sounds like he missed being on vacation just as we would when we have to come back to work or school i'm sure he doesn't have as much freedom to roam within a city just make sure you treat him to as many vacations as you go on he'll look forward to those moments you're a good pet owner Dog training Shaggy dog story Obedience training Guadalupe Mountains National Park The Sims Sonic the Hedgehog Garfield FoxTrot Clinical depression Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban Conker's Bad Fur Day Fancy rat Swimming Xiaolin Showdown Datalore (TNG episode) Guinea pig The Amber Spyglass City of Heroes Appalachian Mountain Club Ferret Dog RuneScape quests Main characters of Fullmetal Alchemist Drowning Craters of the Moon National Monument and Preserve Labrador Retriever Series finale Dead Like Me Characters in the Smurfs Aladdin (1992 film) Auburn University Aerosmith Make money fast Everwood One Tree Hill (TV series) Diving Falconry Paranoia Agent Camp Lazlo Quicksort Los Angeles Clippers Nintendogs Cruising (maritime) Midwestern United States Gary Snyder Chevy Chase Aquaman Futurama (TV series - season 5) Canadian National Exhibition Pet Pok__mon Chronicles Swingout Urbana, Illinois Hearing impairment Wild at Heart (Buffy episode) Long Path Kender The Critic Jason Voorhees Dog (Half-Life 2) Jersey Devil Surveillance The Invisibles Borderline personality disorder Non-native pronunciations of English The Great Brain Hazing Lake Tahoe Spidey Super Stories Kearney, Ontario Wheel of Fortune Random Harvest Trapping Branch predictor Into the Woods The Smoking Room German Shepherd Dog Leash Miss Saigon Dog collar Pet skunk Ko 